rial cultures Lactobacillus bulgaricus and\r\nStreptococcus thermophilus. The culturing process provides the perfect environment for the bacteria to grow, and grow and\r\ngrow... into the millions! While these cultures are growing, they modify the milk and release acids that give yogurt its tartness.\r\nFrog also adds additional cultures such as Lactobacillus acidophilus, Lactobacillus lactis and Bifidobacterium when making\r\nyogurt. We never heat treat yogurt after it is made. Heating would kill the cultures and you would lose the potential benefits.\r\nAt Frog, we make yogurt and then add sweeteners, flavors, and other ingredients to produce the variety of soft serve\r\nfrozen yogurt flavors that are such a delicious treat.'),(22335,1407,'_footer_0_text','field_60'),(22336,1407,'footer_1_title','What is the \"Live and Active Cultures Seal\"?'),(22337,1407,'_footer_1_title','field_59'),(22338,1407,'footer_1_text','In order to carry the National Yogurt Association’s Live & Active Culture (LAC) seal, frozen yogurt must contain at least\r\n10 million cultures per gram at the time of manufacture. To learn more about yogurt and the NYA’s LAC seal visit: www.\r\naboutyogurt.com'),(22339,1407,'_footer_1_text','field_60'),(22340,1407,'footer','2'),(22341,1407,'_footer','field_58'),(22342,1407,'custom_title',''),(22343,1407,'_custom_title','field_39'),(22344,1407,'subtitle',''),(22345,1407,'_subtitle','field_40'),(22346,1409,'additional_image',''),(22347,1409,'_additional_image','field_42'),(22348,1409,'form','card'),(22349,1409,'_form','field_45'),(22350,1409,'form_caption','Balance Check'),(22351,1409,'_form_caption','field_46'),(22352,1409,'form_success','Your card is now registered'),(22353,1409,'_form_success','field_56'),(22354,1409,'help_image','1370'),(22355,1409,'_help_image','field_51e6e7e07456f'),(22356,1409,'custom_title','enjoy the perks of the frog card'),(22357,1409,'_custom_title','field_39'),(22358,1409,'subtitle',''),(22359,1409,'_subtitle','field_40'),(2